<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMarshall_Kirk_McKusick.2C_Keith_Bostic.2C_Michael_J._Karels.2C_and_John_S._Quarterman1996">Marshall Kirk McKusick, Keith Bostic, Michael J. Karels, and John S. Quarterman (1996). "Local Filesystems". <i>The Design and Implementation of the 4.4BSD Operating System</i>. <a href="/wiki/Addison-Wesley" title="Addison-Wesley" class="mw-redirect">Addison-Wesley</a>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0201549794" class="internal">ISBN 0-201-54979-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Local+Filesystems&amp;rft.atitle=The+Design+and+Implementation+of+the+4.4BSD+Operating+System&amp;rft.aulast=Marshall+Kirk+McKusick%2C+Keith+Bostic%2C+Michael+J.+Karels%2C+and+John+S.+Quarterman&amp;rft.au=Marshall+Kirk+McKusick%2C+Keith+Bostic%2C+Michael+J.+Karels%2C+and+John+S.+Quarterman&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BAddison-Wesley%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-201-54979-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Unix_File_System"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMarshall_Kirk_McKusick.2C_Keith_Bostic.2C_Michael_J._Karels.2C_and_John_S._Quarterman1996">Marshall Kirk McKusick, Keith Bostic, Michael J. Karels, and John S. Quarterman (1996). "Local Filestores". <i>The Design and Implementation of the 4.4BSD Operating System</i>. Addison-Wesley. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0201549794" class="internal">ISBN 0-201-54979-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Local+Filestores&amp;rft.atitle=The+Design+and+Implementation+of+the+4.4BSD+Operating+System&amp;rft.aulast=Marshall+Kirk+McKusick%2C+Keith+Bostic%2C+Michael+J.+Karels%2C+and+John+S.+Quarterman&amp;rft.au=Marshall+Kirk+McKusick%2C+Keith+Bostic%2C+Michael+J.+Karels%2C+and+John+S.+Quarterman&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.pub=Addison-Wesley&amp;rft.isbn=0-201-54979-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Unix_File_System"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal">Marshall Kirk McKusick and Gregory R. Ganger (1999). "<a href="http://www.usenix.org/publications/library/proceedings/usenix99/full_papers/mckusick/mckusick.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.usenix.org/publications/library/proceedings/usenix99/full_papers/mckusick/mckusick.pdf" rel="nofollow">Soft Updates: A Technique for Eliminating Most Synchronous Writes in the Fast Filesystem</a>" (PDF). <i>Proceedings of the FREENIX Track: 1999 USENIX Annual Technical Conference</i>: 1–18. <span class="reference-accessdate">Retrieved on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-12-30"><a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a>-<a href="/wiki/December_30" title="December 30">12-30</a></span></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=proceeding&amp;rft.btitle=Proceedings+of+the+FREENIX+Track%3A+1999+USENIX+Annual+Technical+Conference&amp;rft.atitle=Soft+Updates%3A+A+Technique+for+Eliminating+Most+Synchronous+Writes+in+the+Fast+Filesystem&amp;rft.au=Marshall+Kirk+McKusick+and+Gregory+R.+Ganger&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.pages=1%26ndash%3B18&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.usenix.org%2Fpublications%2Flibrary%2Fproceedings%2Fusenix99%2Ffull_papers%2Fmckusick%2Fmckusick.pdf"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal">Marshall Kirk McKusick (2002). "<a href="http://www.usenix.org/publications/library/proceedings/bsdcon02/mckusick/mckusick_html/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.usenix.org/publications/library/proceedings/bsdcon02/mckusick/mckusick_html/index.html" rel="nofollow">Running "fsck" in the Background</a>". <i>Proceedings of the BSDCon 2002</i>: 55–64.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=proceeding&amp;rft.btitle=Proceedings+of+the+BSDCon+2002&amp;rft.atitle=Running+%22fsck%22+in+the+Background&amp;rft.au=Marshall+Kirk+McKusick&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pages=55%26ndash%3B64&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.usenix.org%2Fpublications%2Flibrary%2Fproceedings%2Fbsdcon02%2Fmckusick%2Fmckusick_html%2Findex.html"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>The Linux Documentation Project's <a href="http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/Filesystems-HOWTO-9.html#ffs" class="external text" title="http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/Filesystems-HOWTO-9.html#ffs" rel="nofollow">Filesystems HOWTO: FFS</a>. Note that the distinction this draws between FFS and UFS is wrong; both terms are used at present and have been used in the past.</li>
<li><a href="http://sixshooter.v6.thrupoint.net/jeroen/faq.html#UFS-DIFF-FFS" class="external text" title="http://sixshooter.v6.thrupoint.net/jeroen/faq.html#UFS-DIFF-FFS" rel="nofollow">Little UFS2 FAQ: What is the difference between UFS and FFS?</a> Note that this gets the relationship between FFS and UFS backwards; see the "Local Filesystems" chapter of <i>The Design and Implementation of the 4.4BSD Operating System</i>, which refers to the upper layer as UFS, and the "Local Filestores" chapter, which refers to the lower layer as FFS.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.informit.com/content/images/0131482092/samplechapter/mcdougall_ch15.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.informit.com/content/images/0131482092/samplechapter/mcdougall_ch15.pdf" rel="nofollow">The Sun Solaris UFS implementation</a> chapter of the <i>Solaris Internals: Solaris 10 and OpenSolaris Kernel Architecture, Second Edition</i> book by Richard McDougall, Jim Mauro <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0131482092" class="internal">ISBN 0-13-148209-2</a></li>
<li><cite id="Reference-idAllen2005">Allen, Hervey (2005-06-20). "Introduction to FreeBSD, PacNOG I Workshop, Additional Topics", Network Startup Resource Center.</cite> <span class="PDFlink"><a href="http://www.pacnog.org/pacnog1/day1/freebsd/intro-freebsd-additional-topics.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.pacnog.org/pacnog1/day1/freebsd/intro-freebsd-additional-topics.pdf" rel="nofollow"><i>UFS2 and Soft Updates make for a powerful combination</i>, page 23, retrieved on 2007-11-04</a></span><span style="font-size:smaller;"><a href="/wiki/Portable_Document_Format" title="Portable Document Format">PDF</a>&#160;(385&#160;KB)</span></li>
</ul>
